<item>
 <title>The Language of Hip Hop: Should Artists be held Accountable for their Words?</title>
 <link>http://www.brown.edu/Departments/Political_Theory_Project/janus/events/the_language_of_hip_hop_should_artists_be_held_accountable_for_their_words</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-tagline&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Can Artists be held Accountable for their Words?        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-datetime field-field-je-date&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label-inline-first&quot;&gt;
              Date:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
                    &lt;span class=&quot;date-display-single&quot;&gt;Thursday, February 23, 2012 - &lt;span class=&quot;date-display-start&quot;&gt;4:00pm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;date-display-separator&quot;&gt; - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;date-display-end&quot;&gt;6:00pm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-je-speakers&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                      &lt;div class=&quot;field-label-inline-first&quot;&gt;
              Speakers:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
                    Michael Eric Dyson and Cornel West        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An international phenomenon, hip hop music has transformed the artistic and cultural landscape of our generation. While it is widely accepted as influential and pervasive, hip hop remains the subject of heated debate and criticism for its controversial content and language. With allegations of its effect on perceptions of sexism, race, and violence, is there a case for censorship regarding this art form? In other words: To what extent can artists be held accountable for their words?&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
