&lt;p&gt;The 2010 healthcare law, the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act, includes an individual healthcare mandate requiring Americans to obtain health insurance by 2014 or pay a fine. Opponents of healthcare argue this is beyond Congress&#039;s power. This Janus Lecture will address the question: Is the Healthcare Mandate Constitutional?&lt;/p&gt;
